post_text: Kokomo School Corporation will be cancelling classes on Tuesday, November 19, 2019. The technical reason for the cancellation is staff shortages that prevent a safe and adequate operation of our schools; however, the root cause is inadequate public education funding from State-elected leaders... and the unfortunate need for Indiana educators to drive to Indianapolis to remind elected leaders of the legislators' recent public education funding failures.
text: Kokomo School Corporation will be cancelling classes on Tuesday, November 19, 2019. The technical reason for the cancellation is staff shortages that prevent a safe and adequate operation of our schools; however, the root cause is inadequate public education funding from State-elected leaders... and the unfortunate need for Indiana educators to drive to Indianapolis to remind elected leaders of the legislators' recent public education funding failures.

post_text: Grateful for our international students who have chosen to study at Kokomo this year. Countries represented include Thailand, Mozambique, Spain, Brazil, Ghana, Vietnam, Macedonia, China, Mexico, Tajikistan, Germany, South Korea, Albania, Senegal, and Italy...and more. Some of the students were able to join me for dinner tonight, and I greatly appreciate their confidence, determination and overall drive in reaching their dreams. Welcome to Kokomo!
